        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 8 at 4:53PM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 453 PM CDT/353 PM MDT/, Doppler radar was tracking a strong
thunderstorm 15 miles north of Morristown, or 24 miles northeast of
Lemmon, moving southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Leith, Heil, and Standing Rock.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
